<p>Open Library aims to have a web page for every book ever published. This ambitious project allows you to borrow eBooks for free. With a simple sign-up process, you can access a massive library of novels, ranging from classics to contemporary works. Open Library also gives you the option to contribute by adding new titles and editing book information, fostering a community of readers and writers.</p>
<h3>LibriVox</h3>
<p>If you enjoy audiobooks, LibriVox is the perfect platform for you. It provides free audiobooks of public domain novels, read by volunteers from all around the world. You can listen to classic novels while on the go or at home. The selection is vast, with titles from authors like Tolstoy, Poe, and Shelly. The user-friendly interface makes it easy to find and download your favorite titles.</p>
