<p>ManyBooks is another excellent resource for free novels. It offers over 50,000 eBooks, including a mix of classics and newer self-published works. The website allows you to browse by genre, author, or even popularity. A standout feature is the daily selections that introduce new titles regularly, providing you with endless options for your next read.</p>
<h3>Wattpad</h3>
<p>If you’re looking for contemporary stories, Wattpad borders on social media for readers and writers alike. It has millions of user-generated stories, including genres like romance, horror, and fantasy. This vibrant community allows you to interact with authors by commenting on their stories, providing a unique reading experience. Best of all, you can read stories online for free and even discover new writers on their creative journey.</p>
